cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the task of Vision-and-Language Navigation (VLN), which involves natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture that incorporates multiple modalities, including images, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the task of VLN involves navigation, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics).
